childMdx.rawBody:
The body of an `if`-statement either executes, or it does not execute.

Students might mistake `if`-statements for `while`-statements.

### Conditional: Execute body zero or one times

```python
if a > 0:
    a = a - 1
```

```mermaid
flowchart TD;
    idIf{a > 0}
    idThen[a = a - 1]
    idExit((x))
    idIf-->|true|idThen;
    idIf-->|false|idExit;
    idThen-->idExit;
```

### Loop: Execute body zero or more times

```python
while a > 0:
    a = a - 1
```

```mermaid
flowchart TD;
    idWhile{a > 0}
    idBody[a = a - 1]
    idExit2((x))
    idWhile-->|true|idBody;
    idWhile-->|false|idExit2;
    idBody-->idWhile;
```

